				</ukm:Metadata><Secondary><Body DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2013/376/body" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/body" NumberOfProvisions="133" RestrictStartDate="2026-04-30"><Part DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2013/376/part/6" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/part/6" NumberOfProvisions="35" id="part-6" RestrictStartDate="2025-07-22"><Number><Strong>PART 6</Strong></Number><Title>CALCULATION OF CAPITAL AND INCOME</Title><Chapter DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2013/376/part/6/chapter/3" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/part/6/chapter/3" NumberOfProvisions="10" id="part-6-chapter-3" RestrictStartDate="2024-04-01"><Number>CHAPTER 3</Number><Title>UNEARNED INCOME</Title><Pblock DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2013/376/part/6/chapter/3/crossheading/general" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/part/6/chapter/3/crossheading/general" NumberOfProvisions="3" id="part-6-chapter-3-crossheading-general" RestrictStartDate="2014-11-26"><Title><Emphasis>General</Emphasis></Title><P1group RestrictStartDate="2013-04-29"><Title>Assumed yield from capital</Title><P1 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2013/376/regulation/72" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/regulation/72" id="regulation-72">
<Pnumber>72</Pnumber>
<P1para>
<P2 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2013/376/regulation/72/1" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/regulation/72/1" id="regulation-72-1">
<Pnumber>1</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text>A person's capital is to be treated as yielding a monthly income of £4.35 for each £250 in excess of £6,000 and £4.35 for any excess which is not a complete £250.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2013/376/regulation/72/2" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/regulation/72/2" id="regulation-72-2">
<Pnumber>2</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text>Paragraph (1) does not apply where the capital is disregarded or the actual income from that capital is taken into account under regulation 66(1)(i) (income from an annuity) or (j) (income from a trust).</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
<P2 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2013/376/regulation/72/3" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/uksi/2013/376/regulation/72/3" id="regulation-72-3">
<Pnumber>3</Pnumber>
<P2para>
<Text>Where a person's capital is treated as yielding income, any actual income derived from that capital, for example rental, interest or dividends, is to be treated as part of the person's capital from the day it is due to be paid to the person.</Text>
</P2para>
</P2>
</P1para>
</P1></P1group></Pblock></Chapter></Part></Body></Secondary></Legislation>